      <h3>About CST Academics</h3>
  <p>
    The College of Science and Technology (CST) offers undergraduate programs in Civil, Electrical, Electronics and Communication, Information Technology, Architecture, Instrumentation and Control Engineering, and Engineering Geology.
  </p>
  <p>
    It also provides a Master's program in Renewable Energy and Construction Management. The curriculum emphasizes practical learning, research, and internationalization to meet Bhutan’s evolving needs.
  </p>
  <p>
    CST conducts short-term training and workshops, especially for in-service civil servants, and maintains high-quality teaching and research standards.
  </p>

  <hr style="margin: 1.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />

  <h4>Admission Eligibility</h4>
  <p><strong>Note:</strong> <span style="color: red;">Students without CID are not eligible for admission.</span></p>

  <h5>Architecture Programme:</h5>
  <ul>
    <li>Class XII pass with minimum 50% in Physics, Chemistry, Math, English, and a pass in Dzongkha.</li>
    <li>Must pass an <strong>Aptitude Test</strong> with at least 50% to qualify.</li>
    <li><strong>Ability Ratings:</strong> Math (5), Physics (5), Chemistry (2), English (3), Aptitude Test</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Engineering Programmes:</h5>
  <ul>
    <li>Class XII pass with minimum 50% in Physics, Chemistry, Math, English, and a pass in Dzongkha.</li>
    <li>Must pass an <strong>Entrance Test</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>Ability Ratings:</strong> Math (5), Physics (5), Chemistry (4), English (3), One other subject (1)</li>
  </ul>

  <hr style="margin: 1.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />

  <h4>Programmes Offered</h4>
  <p>
    The College offers:
    <ul>
      <li>Master of Engineering in Renewable Energy</li>
      <li>Masters in Construction Management</li>
      <li>Four-year undergraduate engineering programs in:
        <ul>
          <li>Civil Engineering</li>
          <li>Electrical Engineering</li>
          <li>Electronics & Communication Engineering</li>
          <li>Information Technology</li>
          <li>Engineering Geology</li>
          <li>Instrumentation & Control Engineering</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Five-year undergraduate program in Architecture</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <p>
    Capacity-building programs are also offered for in-service personnel holding diplomas in Civil, Electrical, ECE, and IT. These programs consider prior learning and typically have a reduced duration of one year.
  </p>

